title: For Sale:  120rds Assorted 7.62x54 Ammo, Yellow/Silver Tip, M39, Tracer, Bulgarian Brass
postcontent:
Here's 120 rounds of the 7.62x54 ammo that you just don't see much of anymore.

40 rounds of Hungarian steel core, heavy ball (182 grain) with the silver/yellow tip. This ammo packs a lot more punch than the standard 147 grain light ball and it's always been noticeably more accurate in my rifles. Plus it penetrates like crazy. The only drawback at all is that recoil is heavier.

40 rounds East German M39. This ammo was originally designed as training ammo for their machine guns. The theory was that the special black, steel jacketed, steel core 124 grain bullet would travel less far than the normal 182 grain ammo used at the time. However there is nothing underpowered at all about this ammo and it'll shoot through 1/4" steel plate at 100 yards. The big advantage to this ammo is that felt recoil is about half of what the 147 grain light ball ammo is. Therefore it's excellent for the younger shooters and the ladies who would like to shoot your Mosin.

20 rounds orange tip Red Tracer. The bullet lights up at around 100 yards out, and traces for about 700 - 800 yards. It's visible during the day, but it's spectacular at night.

20 rounds early 50's Bulgarian brass case light ball. This ammo is bright, shiny and looks like it was made yesterday, and I've always felt brass case ammo functioned smoother/better than any of the steel case stuff. 

I'm selling this ammo as one lot for $100 with pickup in the Brandon area. You must be at least 18 to purchase this ammo. I can ship at buyers expense via UPS ground.

Originally designed for the American market, the USP (Universal Self-loading Pistol) has found international acceptance as an accurate and ultra-reliable handgun. Features favored by U.S. law enforcement and military users provided much of the design criteria for the USP. The controls are uniquely American, influenced by such famous designs as the Government Model 1911 pistol.

All USPs use a fiber-reinforced polymer frame stiffened by stainless steel inserts at areas subject to stress and friction. HK pioneered this use of polymer materials in the production of handguns more than 30 years ago with the development of the VP70Z and P9S pistols.

Using a modified Browning-type action with a special patented recoil reduction system, the USP recoil reduction system reduces recoil effects on pistol components and also lowers the recoil forces felt by the shooter. This same recoil reduction system has been tested and proven in the HK Mark 23 pistol developed for the U.S. Special Operations Command. The USP recoil reduction system is insensitive to ammunition types and requires no special adjustment or maintenance. It functions effectively in all USP models.

The modular design of the USP's internal components allows the control lever function to be switched from the left to the right side of the pistol for left-handed shooters. The USP can also be converted from one type of trigger firing mode to another. This includes combination double-action and single-action (DA/SA) modes and double action only (DAO) modes.
